    <body>
        <h1 style="margin-top: 0;"><img src="/logo.png" alt="gamePLUS"></h1><hr><a href="/">← Go back to home page</a>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is gamePLUS?</h2>
        <p>At ninePLUS, we're building a chat app called <a href="https://www.nineplus.sh/quarky">Quarky</a>.<br><a href="https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/7931156448919-Activity-Status-Recent-Activity">Similarly to Discord</a>, Quarky can display what game you're playing on your profile.</p>
        <p>We needed a way to detect what games are running, and this is that.<br>gamePLUS stores the icon, executables (<code><%= sampleGame.executables[0].name %></code>) and name (<i><%= sampleGame.name %></i>) for games.</p>
        <p>This way, you can see exactly what someone's playing:</p>
        <div class="gaming">
            <p>Playing a game</p>
            <div class="gamewrap">
                <img class="gamelogo" src="/game/<%= sampleGame._id %>/icon">
                <div class="gamedata">
                    <b><%= sampleGame.name %></b>
                    <p>12:34 elapsed</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="gamedisclaim">Game chosen at random. ninePLUS does not own the rights to <%= sampleGame.name %>.<br>For demonstrational purposes only.</p>

        <h2 id="submit-game">A game is missing or the information is wrong.</h2>
        <p>Use the <a href="https://www.nineplus.sh/support.html">ninePLUS contact form</a> and suggest change(s) there.<br>Alternatively, relevant pages will have the contact form in the bottom right corner.<br>Alternatively alternatively, you can join the <a href="https://discord.gg/lit-devs-868937321402204220">LIT Devs Discord</a> and ping Hakase there.</p>
        <p>If suggesting a new game and it's on Steam, just send the store page link.<br>Otherwise, send the name, icon, and executable (<code><%= sampleGame.executables[0].name %></code>).</p>

        <h2 id="use-gameplus">I want to use the gamePLUS database.</h2>
        <p>Making the database easy to use is not on our priority list right now, so we wouldn't recommend it.<br>Strictly speaking you can use the <a href="/api/games">/api/games</a> endpoint to get JSON output, but only use it for pet projects and cache heavily.</p>
        <p>For projects with more than like five users and/or commercial projects, <a href="https://www.nineplus.sh/support.html">contact ninePLUS</a>.</p>

